    <!-- INGREDIENT DEEP DIVE -->
    <div class="ing-box">
      <h3>Pre-Workout Ingredients: What the Science Says</h3>
      <p>Not all pre-workout ingredients are created equal. Here is what peer-reviewed research confirms about the key compounds found in pre-workout gummies, including the doses required for measurable performance benefits.</p>

      <div class="vs-strip">
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Caffeine</strong>
          <p>The most-studied ergogenic aid. Effective at 3-6mg/kg body weight (150-300mg for most adults). Improves strength, power, endurance, and reaction time. Peak blood levels at 30-60 minutes post-ingestion. Tolerance develops with chronic use.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Beta-Alanine</strong>
          <p>Increases intramuscular carnosine, buffering hydrogen ions during high-intensity exercise. Clinical dose: 3.2g/day for 4-12 weeks. Benefits are cumulative, not acute — daily consistency matters more than timing. The tingling is harmless.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>L-Citrulline</strong>
          <p>Converts to arginine and then nitric oxide. Clinical dose: 3-6g for acute performance benefits. Most gummies deliver 500mg-1.5g, which is sub-clinical but may still contribute to NO production when combined with dietary nitrate sources.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Beetroot / Dietary Nitrates</strong>
          <p>Natural nitric oxide precursor. Studies show beetroot supplementation improves time-trial performance by 1-3% and reduces oxygen cost of exercise. Effective at 300-600mg nitrate content, equivalent to approximately 500ml beetroot juice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

